        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:17PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wingdale, or near Sherman, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danbury, Sherman, Brookfield, and New Fairfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
